---
title: Cherry Ancho Glazed Chicken with Almond & Scallion Rice
description: Our chefs elevate juicy seared chicken cutlets with a rich, flavorful glaze of bright, tart cherry jam and dried cherries swirled with smoky-sweet ancho chili powder and butter. Serve it atop a bed of fluffy, almond- and scallion-studded rice for a spin on the classic pairing of chicken and rice that simply can’t be beat.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/65f9d597c9eee2bcbf31fdf5-5c7e5a3e.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/65f9d597c9eee2bcbf31fdf5.pdf
time required: 20 minutes
cuisine: European
nutrition:
  calories: 560 kcal
  fat: 16 g
  saturated fat: 5 g
  carbohydrates: 63 g
  sugar: 22 g
  protein: 37 g
  fiber: 2 g
  sodium: 290 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/cherry-ancho-glazed-chicken-65f9d597c9eee2bcbf31fdf5
author: Sara Heilman
course: main course
servings: 2
---

In a #small pot{}, combine @white rice{1/2%cup}, 3⁄4 cup water (1 1⁄2 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to use in Step 6.

Meanwhile, wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; place between two large pieces of #plastic wrap{}. Pound with a #mallet{} or #rolling pin{} until chicken is about 1⁄2 inch thick. Season all over with @ancho chili powder{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> TIP: Lower heat if chicken begins to brown too quickly.

While chicken cooks, in a #small bowl{}, whisk together scallion whites, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @cherry jam{1}, @dried cherries{1%oz}, and 1/2 cup water (3⁄4 cup for 4 servings).

Once chicken is cooked through, reduce heat under pan to medium low. Add cherry glaze and @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Cook, turning chicken occasionally, until glaze has thickened slightly and chicken is evenly coated, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in scallion greens and @sliced almonds{1/2%oz}.

Divide rice between plates; top with glazed chicken. Spoon any remaining glaze from pan over chicken and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.